zing, the best outcome that I could of imagined, Mitch was so supportive, highly recommend”\n\n#### Jed Earle\n\n15 December 2024\n\n“Mitch and the Team at Garde Wilson provided exceptional second to none service, they were extremely professional and comforting...”\n\n#### Celeste Earle\n\n11 December 2024\n\n“I had the privilege of working with Garde Wilson Criminal Lawyers during a very difficult time, and I cannot...”\n\n#### Vishal\n\n01 December 2024\n\n“Thank you to Mitch and team. You achieved the impossible, great outcome. Highly recommend\nif anyone requires representation.”\n\n#### Andre Spiteri\n\n9 August 2023\n\n“Wow! This team are incredible!\nWith 48hrs notice Mitch had my partner sorted and had barrister Hazel appear on his behalf\ntoday...”\n\n#### Rel KC\n\n17 November 2023\n\n“I had the privilege of being represented by MITCH AND ZARAH AT GARDE WILSON LAWYERS as my\ndefence lawyer.”\n\n#### Sachin Sachdeva\n\n6 October 2023\n\n“I am very pleased with my experience, they are very professional and they did a very well job\nto support me all through my case.”\n\n#### Baljinder Singh\n\n11 August 2023\n\n“I will highly recommend them to my friends or family if in need. Mitch was there at every step\nwith the barristers.”\n\n#### Harman SIngh\n\n9 August 2023\n\n[![testmonials](<Base64-Image-Removed>)](https://www.google.com/search?sca_esv=d425b5dac0dba72a&cs=0&si=APYL9bs7Hg2KMLB-4tSoTdxuOx8BdRvHbByC_AuVpNyh0x2KzTOGNBq2bNt0r93V8P0p9Gulbd3v8N6wK5E_BZGDcb71rqiedqE7ZlQM2_6iUHqMAXJ2_wUyVmn4Dl27LJsg4YxKgVfOOxK-Zn-ifvSn9s10DSpYew%3D%3D&q=Garde+Wilson+Criminal+Lawyers+Reviews&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjn1ePx3YOMAxUwr1YBHQ9yOrsQ0bkNegQILBAE&biw=1440&bih=677&dpr=2)\n\n[Google Reviews](https://www.google.com/search?sca_esv=d425b5dac0dba72a&cs=0&si=APYL9bs7Hg2KMLB-4tSoTdxuOx8BdRvHbByC_AuVpNyh0x2KzTOGNBq2bNt0r93V8P0p9Gulbd3v8N6wK5E_BZGDcb71rqiedqE7ZlQM2_6iUHqMAXJ2_wUyVmn4Dl27LJsg4YxKgVfOOxK-Zn-ifvSn9s10DSpYew%3D%3D&q=Garde+Wilson+Criminal+Lawyers+Reviews&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjn1ePx3YOMAxUwr1YBHQ9yOrsQ0bkNegQILBAE&biw=1440&bih=677&dpr=2)\n\n4.9\n\n![testmonials](<Base64-Image-Removed>)\n\nBased on 186 reviews\n\nmeet our team\n\n## Choose What Is Right, Choose Garde Wilson Lawyers\n\n![Criminal defence lawyers who fight for you. Garde Wilson Lawyers.](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/profile-2-1.webp)\n\n## GARDE WILSON\n\n### ZARAH GARDE-WILSON\n\nBarrister & solicitor\n\nCriminal defence law expert renowned for handling tough cases and championing her client’s rights before the courts.\n\n![home-team-section](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/profile-2.webp)\n\n## AMANDA O’BRIEN\n\n### Amanda O’Brien\n\nSenior Paralegal\n\nAmanda expertly supports our Gold Coast team and as a clerk at Garde Wilson Lawyers, she is entrusted to help our clients through a challenging period.\n\n![home-team-section](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/profile-3.webp)\n\n## RAY RAHEEM\n\n### Ray Raheem\n\nParalegal\n\nCurrently in the final year of his law degree, which he will complete in late 2025, Ray brings a profound passion for the law and a genuine commitment to helping people.\n\n![Home](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/criminal-court.webp)\n\n## Go to Court with the Leading Melbourne Criminal Lawyers by Your Side\n\nIf you are facing criminal charges ranging from simple traffic matters through to the most serious offences, we provide the services you need to secure the best outcome.\n\nOur 24 hour emergency helpline will provide you with the immediate advice you need, ensuring you avoid making any mistakes, in the critical first few hours of arrest, that will damage your case.\n\ngive us a call\n\nour process\n\n## What happens when I’m charged?\n\n![Initial Interview](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lawyer-interview.webp)\n\n### 01 Initial Interview\n\nThis takes place either on the side of the road or at the police\nstation when the police first contact you about an alleged\noffence and your involvement in it.\n\nYou should always seek legal advice before speaking to any\nmember of the Victorian police when concerned with an\nallegation.\n\n![You Are Charged](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/hancupped.webp)\n\n### 02 You Are Charged\n\nOnce police have completed their interview with you, if they\nfeel they have sufficient evidence to have the allegations found\nproven, they will charge you.\n\nThey will issue you with paperwork outlining the offences you\nare charged with. This paperwork is vital to our defence.\n\n![Summon Or Bail?](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/trial-court.webp)\n\n### 03 Summon Or Bail?\n\nWhether you are summoned to court or bailed to appear at court\ndepends on the charges.\n\nBail is when the police have released you into the custody of a\nperson who gives an undertaking that you will appear at a\nspecified time and place to answer the charge against you. Have\nyou been bailed to appear at court?\n\n![Court Appearance](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/lawyer-defending-in-trial-court.webp)\n\n### 04 Court Appearance\n\nThe final step is attending court for your case to be heard by a\nmagistrate or judge. Any case that goes before a court is\nserious. Court opens at 9am each day and we will be there to\nensure you do not face this stressful task alone.\n\nWe speak to the prosecutors, court staff and manage the whole\nprocess by standing by you and speaking on your behalf for your\nbest interests.\n\n01 Initial Interview\n\n02 You Are Charged\n\n03 Summon Or Bail?\n\n04 Court Appearance\n\n01Initial Interview\n\n![](<Base64-Image-Removed>)\n\nThis takes place either on the side of the road or at the police station when the police first contact you about an alleged offence and your involvement in it.\n\nYou should always seek legal advice before speaking to any member of the Victorian police when concerned with an allegation.\n\n02You Are Charged\n\n![](<Base64-Image-Removed>)\n\nOnce police have completed their interview with you, if they feel they have sufficient evidence to have the allegations found proven, they will charge you.\n\nThey will issue you with paperwork outlining the offences you are charged with. This paperwork is vital to our defence.\n\n03Summon Or Bail?\n\n![](<Base64-Image-Removed>)\n\nWhether you are summoned to court or bailed to appear at court depends on the charges.\n\nBail is when the police have released you into the custody of a person who gives an undertaking that you will appear at a specified time and place to answer the charge against you. Have you been bailed to appear at court?\n\n04Court Appearance\n\n![](<Base64-Image-Removed>)\n\nThe final step is attending court for your case to be heard by a magistrate or judge. Any case that goes before a court is serious. Court opens at 9am each day and we will be there to ensure you do not face this stressful task alone.\n\nWe speak to the prosecutors, court staff and manage the whole process by standing by you and speaking on your behalf for your best interests.\n\n![leading criminal barrister](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Gravel-Block-animation.webp)\n\nABOUT US\n\n## We are experts in criminal defence, it's the only law we practice\n\nFirm founder, Zarah Garde-Wilson is a Barrister and Solicitor of the Supreme Court of Victoria and is a registered practitioner with the High Court of Australia.\n\nWith over 20 years experience as a Melbourne criminal lawyer, Zarah has a track record of fighting and winning complex criminal law cases and has established a reputation as one of Australia’s most sought-after and trusted criminal defence lawyers.\n\nknow more about us\n\n## it’s FREE to find out where you stand\n\nCall us on [0400 002 188](tel:0400 002 188)\n\nor Click here\n\n## Why Choose Garde Wilson Lawyers?\n\n## EXPERience\n\nMelbourne criminal defence specialist with more than 20 years of successful practice in defending charges ranging from minor driving offences to murder – Garde Wilson Lawyers carry an unrivalled tenure in defence against all criminal offences.\n\nNever leave your future or freedom in the hands of anyone but the best. Avoid jail, minimise or avoid licence loss and call our legal team today.\n\n## Reputation​\n\nGarde-Wilson Lawyers reputation in matters of criminal defence is unmatched.\n\nLed by founding partner, Zarah Garde-Wilson, our team has provided advocacy and representation in some of Australia’s toughest cases, utilising unparalleled knowledge of the criminal justice system, courtroom prowess, and depth of expertise.\n\n## Focus on You\n\nWhen you have Garde Wilson Lawyers behind you in court, you have a team of professional legal and administrative personnel at your disposal to best help you achieve an outstanding result for your case.\n\nFrequently asked question\n\n## Do you still have questions?\n\n01Does Garde Wilson Lawyers handle both traffic offences and serious criminal charges in Victoria?\n\nYes. Garde Wilson Lawyers represent clients across the full spectrum of criminal matters — from traffic and driving offences, including drink and drug driving, to serious indictable crimes such as assault, drug trafficking, sexual offences, and homicide. No matter the charge, our team provides strong, experienced defence and clear guidance at every stage of the process.\n\n02What questions should I ask when contacting a criminal defence lawyer in Melbourne?\n\nIf you’re calling a firm like Garde Wilson Lawyers in Melbourne about a criminal defence matter, it’s important to ask the right questions to understand your options and feel confident in your representation. We recommend asking:\n\nHave you handled cases like mine in Victorian courts before?\n\nWhat’s your approach to defending this type of charge?\n\nBased on your experience, what are the possible outcomes in my situation?\n\nHow are your legal fees structured — do you offer fixed or capped fees?\n\nWhat are the next steps if I decide to proceed with your firm?\n\nIs there anything urgent I should do before my first court date?\n\nWho will be my main point of contact throughout the process?\n\nHow often will I receive updates about my case?\n\nDo you provide after-hours or emergency legal support?\n\nWhat should I bring or prepare before our first consultation?\n\nThese questions will help you make an informed decision and ensure you’re working with a lawyer who’s experienced, transparent, and committed to protecting your rights.\n\n03What steps should I take right away if I’m arrested or charged with a criminal offence in Melbourne?\n\nIf you’re arrested or charged in Melbourne, contact a [criminal defence lawyer](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/contact-us/) immediately. Avoid answering police questions or signing any statements until you’ve received legal advice. Anything you say or do can be used against you later, so having an experienced lawyer by your side from the start is the best way to protect your rights and guide your next steps.\n\n04What are the chances of avoiding a criminal conviction for a first-time offence?\n\nIf it’s your first offence, you may be eligible for a diversion program or another sentencing option that avoids a criminal conviction. The outcome depends on the type of offence, the circumstances of your case, and your personal history. An experienced criminal lawyer can assess your situation, negotiate on your behalf, and help you explore every opportunity to keep your record clean.\n\n05I live in regional Victoria — can Garde Wilson Lawyers still represent me?\n\nYes. Garde Wilson Lawyers represent clients across all parts of Victoria, not just Melbourne. Our team regularly appears in regional courts and can provide legal advice, support, and representation remotely or in person. No matter where you’re based, you’ll have direct access to experienced criminal defence lawyers who will guide you through every stage of your case.\n\n06Will I know the total cost of representation upfront?\n\nYes. We offer affordable fixed fees, giving you full clarity and confidence about costs from the beginning.\n\n07How do legislative changes in Victoria, including updates to bail or hoon laws, impact my case?\n\nChanges to Victorian law — such as updates to bail, hoon, or sentencing laws — can directly influence how your case is managed and the penalties that may apply. An experienced criminal defence lawyer will review your situation under the most current legislation to make sure you understand your rights, the possible outcomes, and the best strategy for your defence.\n\n08Can digital evidence, such as mobile phone data or social media posts, be used in a criminal case against me?\n\nYes. Police and prosecutors can use digital evidence — including mobile phone data, text messages, photos, videos, and social media activity — to support their case. It’s important to avoid posting or sharing anything related to your matter and to seek legal advice immediately. Your lawyer can guide you on how to protect your privacy and ensure your rights are protected.\n\n## Why Choose Garde Wilson Lawyers?\n\nWe understand better than most the stress and angst that a criminal charge or circumstance can cause. From the moment you are charged, it is crucial to be informed of your legal rights and have a lawyer made available to you as per the criminal procedure enacted in the Criminal Procedure Act 2009.\n\nWe know the law, the procedure that must be followed and will ensure your liberties, well being and future are taken care of with the utmost professionalism and expertise\n\n![Home](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/2023_criminal_lawyers_award_.webp)\n\nCriminal defence specialist  with more than 20 years of successful practice.\n\nA reputation\nfor winning complex cases and achieving successful outcomes in all courts throughout Australia.\n\nNo judgement, ever!\n\nWe carry each of our clients through the system with care and expertise.\n\nBe careful of lawyers who charge excessive legal fees\nand just plead you guilty. Get sound advice and protect your future.\n\nGarde Wilson Lawyers know the courts,\n\nknow the system and know what is most important to you and your family.\n\nYour case matters,\n\nget the best criminal lawyers in Melbourne to protect your freedom and future.\n\nAffordable Fixed Legal Fees,\n\nwe always keep our fees fixed and see out your case from start to finish.\n\n![Home](<Base64-Image-Removed>)\n\n## IT PAYS TO BE PREPARED\n\n![Home](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/free_courtroom_survival_guide.webp)\n\n## Get your FREE courtroom survival guide HERE\n\ndownload\n\n![Home](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/free_character_reference_here.webp)\n\n## Get your FREE character reference HERE\n\ndownload\n\n## Get a Free Case Assessment\n\nAvoid Jail. Avoid Serious Fines. Get the Best Defence.\n\nFirst Name \\\\*\n\nLast Name \\\\*\n\nPhone Number \\\\*\n\nEmail \\\\*\n\nMessage\n\nUpload your charges or paperwork here\n\nThis site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the Google [Privacy Policy](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/#) and [Terms of Service](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/#) apply.\n\nsend message\n\nOur Offices\n\n## Conveniently Located to Serve Your Legal Needs\n\nWe connect with clients from Victoria and South Eastern Queensland at our Offices in Williams Street, Melbourne City and Cavil Avenue, Surfers Paradise. Garde Wilson Lawyers also serves clients Australia-wide seeking justice from higher courts.\n\n![Home-footer-images](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/img-19.webp)\n\n##### Melbourne CBD, Vic\n\n![Home-footer-images](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/img-20.webp)\n\n##### Surfers Paradise, QLD\n\n![Home-footer-images](https://www.gardewilson.com.au/wp-conten